From: Trung Lê <8@tle.id.au>
Subject: split CDE_DATA_TOP from CDE_INSTALLATION_TOP, finish dt-source
 conversion

The previous patch added a CDE_DATA_TOP configure option but the rest
of the codebase still treated CDE_INSTALLATION_TOP as both prefix and
data namespace. As a result, packagers who passed --prefix=/usr ended
up with /usr/app-defaults, /usr/appconfig, /usr/share/backdrops,
/usr/lib/nls/msg, etc. -- root-level dirs polluting /usr/.

This change wires CDE_DATA_TOP through everywhere data-namespace paths
appear, leaving CDE_INSTALLATION_TOP for binaries / libraries / man.
After this, --with-cde-data-dir=/usr/share/cde keeps everything
arch-independent under /usr/share/cde/.

Concretely:

  $(CDE_INSTALLATION_TOP)/{app-defaults,appconfig,share,infolib,
                            backdrops,palettes,lib/nls,lib/dtudcfonted}
  ->  $(CDE_DATA_TOP)/...
                                    [Makefile.am, ~24 files]

  CDE_INSTALLATION_TOP "<data-suffix>"   in C/C++/headers
  ->  CDE_DATA_TOP "<data-suffix>"      [~29 files / 79 substitutions]

  CDE_INSTALLATION_TOP/<data-suffix>     in tradcpp .src/.dt
  ->  CDE_DATA_TOP/<data-suffix>        [~9 files / 22 substitutions]

  Plus -DCDE_DATA_TOP= added to every Makefile.am that already passes
  -DCDE_INSTALLATION_TOP= so the new C/C++ macro uses compile.

Also folded in:

  programs/types/dtmail.dt -> dtmail.dt.src    (rename + path subst)
  programs/types/dtcm.dt   -> dtcm.dt.src      (rename + path subst)
  programs/types/Makefile.am: add both to BUILT_SOURCES + tradcpp rules

Default behavior is unchanged: with no --with-cde-* overrides,
CDE_DATA_TOP defaults to ${prefix} which keeps the historical
/usr/dt/{app-defaults,appconfig,...} layout.
